Class DivergentAttachmentAnnotationReferences

java.lang.Object
org.odpi.openmetadata.fvt.opentypes.entities.DivergentAttachmentAnnotation.DivergentAttachmentAnnotationReferences
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class DivergentAttachmentAnnotationReferences extends Object implements Serializable
References for entity DivergentAttachmentAnnotation. References are relationships represented as an attribute. Exposing relationships information as references can make the relationships information more digestable.

  • Constructor Details

    • DivergentAttachmentAnnotationReferences

      public DivergentAttachmentAnnotationReferences(String entityGuid, Set<Line> lines)
      We are passed a set of omrs relationships that are associated with a entity DivergentAttachmentAnnotation Each of these relationships should map to a reference (a uniquely named attribute in DivergentAttachmentAnnotation). Relationships have cardinality. There are 2 sorts of cardinality relevant here, whether the relationships can be related to one or many entities.
      Parameters:
      lines - the relationships lines.
      entityGuid - The GUID of the entity.
